<HEADLINE> Indo-British Exhibition to Be Held in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The best of British companies are
signing up for the Indo-British Partnership's "Towards 2000" trade
exhibition, taking place during the queen's state visit to India
in October.
</P>
<P>
Rolls Royce, Smithkline Beecham, International Power Presses,
GEC, ICI, Prudential and National Grid are just some of the 100
names that will play a key role in the 500,000 pound (800,000 US
dollar) exhibition from October 14-18.
</P>
<P>
Smaller and medium-sized companies -- from key target sectors
such as advanced manufacturing, healthcare, infrastructure,
aerospace, environmental technologies, mining and education and
training -- are also signing up.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the event, President of the Board of Trade Margaret
Beckett said today, "Our partnership with India continues to be of
great value and I am delighted that British business is helping us
to celebrate this historical bilateral relationship in this,
India's 50th year of independence.
</P>
<P>
Britain is India's largest foreign investor and this, Beckett
said, "is a unique international platform on which to focus
Britain's commercial expertise to a vital Indian audience."
</P>
<P>
Towards 2000 represents Britain's major investment and
industrial collaboration in India, where it exports 1.8 billion
pounds (2.88 billion US dollars) in goods each year, Beckett
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
