<HEADLINE> Pak Wants to Promote Ties With Britain: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar
Ayub Khan today reaffirmed his country's desire to provide further
impetus to mutual ties and collaboration with Britain.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with visiting British Secretary of State for
Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs Derek Fatchett, Ayub Khan
expressed his appreciation of the Labor government's willingness
to help resolve the Kashmir problem in accordance with U.N.
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Ayub Khan and Fatchett, the first senior official from Britain
to visit Pakistan after the formation of the Labor government,
discussed wide-ranging subjects including foreign policy and
bilateral relations with special reference to economic and
commercial links.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Minister for Water and Power C. Nisar Ali
Khan also held a meeting with Fatchett.
</P>
<P>
They discussed matters of mutual interest with special emphasis
on cooperation between the two countries in the energy sector.
</P>
<P>
Fatchett said there was a lot of scope for expanding economic
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Britain is one of Pakistan's largest trading partners and the
second largest investor in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
