<HEADLINE> IOC Launches Sports Science Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic Committee
has set up a biennial award to honor the scientists who make great
contribution to the development of sports science, the IOC
announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The IOC vice president Alexandre Demerode, who also chairs a
IOC medical body, said the award would encourage the scientific
researches in sports training and competition in addition to other
sports sciences.
</P>
<P>
He said it is a good idea to curb the expansion of doping by
improving the sports results through scientifically-conducted
training and the improvement of sports equipment.
</P>
<P>
He said trainers and athletes should learn more about the
latest scientific training methods.
</P>
<P>
The award will be honoured to the researchers who make
contribution to sports-related fields of biology, medicine,
physiology and psychology.
</P>
<P>
The award, in the form of a gold medal and 250,000
U.S. dollars, will be given during the winter and summer Olympic
Games. 
</P>
