<HEADLINE> South China Province to Expand Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A 777 million-yuan contract to
finance the expansion of Yangpu Port in southernmost China's
Hainan Province was signed here today between the Hainan
Provincial Government and the State Development and Investment
Corp.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of construction on the port, scheduled to
begin at the end of the year, includes the building of three
25,000-ton berths which are expected to have a yearly handling
capacity of 1.2 million tons. The project is scheduled to be
completed by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The cost of the project is divided among three investors, with
four billion Yen of loans from Japan, 64 million yuan from Hainan,
and 330 million yuan from the State Development and Investment
Corp., a policy-oriented organization in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The port, as an important facility in the Yangpu Economic
Development Zone, has an annual handling capacity of one million
tons after its first phase of construction finished in 1991.
</P>
</TEXT>
