<HEADLINE> Speaker of Algeria's National Assembly Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Abdul Qadir Bin Saleh, President
of the National Democratic Assembly, has been elected speaker of the
Algerian People's National Assembly, according to Algerian Radio
today.
</P>
<P>
Following his election last night, Bin Saleh said that Algerian
MPs should endeavor to achieve the expectations of the Algerian
people.
</P>
<P>
He said his task was not an easy one, in view of the new
political structure produced by the legislative elections of June
5. He appealed for the support of all members to help him succeed in
his mission.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Qadir Bin Saleh was the speaker of the transitional
National Assembly, the term of office of which expired before the
elections. The National Democratic Assembly won 155 seats in the
380-seat parliament during the elections. Saleh is a sincere
associate of Algerian President Liamine Zeroual.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that his consultations with the heads of other
parliamentary blocs will take place today for the formation of a
committee that will draft the internal statutes, and an
accreditation committee, besides the remaining parliamentary
structures.
</P>
<P>
The Assembly which has emerged as a result of the legislative
elections of June 5, is the first of its kind in Algeria's history.

/end item/

