<HEADLINE> Two Telecom Giants Jointly Issue Handover Phone Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom and China
Telecom today jointly issued a commemorative phone card set to
celebrate Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
This is the first-ever phone card collection jointly issued by
the two major Asian telecom companies.
</P>
<P>
It comprises eight cards, with four issued by Hongkong Telecom
and four issued by China Telecom.
</P>
<P>
The collection depicts four themes -- "Flames of the Opium
Wars", "Historical Turn", "One Country, Two systems" and "Return
to Her Motherland" with delightful day or night time scenes of
Hong Kong on the reverse side.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Telecom Director of Telecom Enterprises Prudence Chan
said, "The first of July 1997 marks the date when Hong Kong
returns to China, and we are delighted to jointly issue the phone
card set with China Telecom at this historic moment."
</P>
<P>
The collection costs 498 HK dollars (64 US dollars) per set and
has a world-wide limited edition of 404,590 sets. 
