<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kyrkyz President Meets Chinese Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BESHKENT, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Kyrkyz President Askar Akayev
today met Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian, who arrived here
on Monday for a five-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Akayev said that the military confidence building treaty and
the troop reduction agreement signed by China, Russia, Kazakhstan,
Tajikistan and Kyrkyzstan in the past two years have further
improved peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Kyrkyzstan strongly opposes national
splittism, which he said is a major evil of mankind and should be
condemned and fought against.
</P>
<P>
He assured the Chinese minister that Kyrkyzstan will always be
with China in the fight against national splittism.
</P>
<P>
Akayev said that the Kyrkyz people are happy to see Hong Kong
return to the embrace of the motherland and reiterated that Taiwan
and Tibet are inalienable parts of the Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Chi said that the 21 century-oriented good
neighborly and cooperative relations between China and Kyrkyzstan
envisaged by their leaders will turn their 1,100-kilometer-long
common border into a peaceful and friendly one.
</P>
<P>
Chi expressed appreciation for Kyrkyzstan's position on Taiwan
and Tibet issues and its opposition against national splittism.
</P>
</TEXT>
