<HEADLINE> Chongqing Municipality Officially Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China's fourth municipality of
Chongqing was officially established here today, and is already
set to take giant steps in development in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng, who is on an inspection tour in the
city, attended a ceremony held in the municipality's grand hall of
the people, and conveyed congratulations to the 30 million
Chongqing people on behalf of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), the State Council and President
Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing was approved as a provincial-level municipality on
March 14 by the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), the
Chinese legislature. It is the first municipality in China's
central and western region.
</P>
<P>
The youngest municipality aims to quadruple its 1995 gross
domestic product (GDP), which totaled 111.3 billion yuan (about
13.4 billion US dollars), by the year 2010, in order to become the
leading economic center in southwest China with the forming of a
group of new industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
