<HEADLINE> Deng's Theory on Reunification of Motherland Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese officials from the
Party central committee and the State Council held a forum here
today together with experts on political theory to discuss Deng
Xiaoping's theories on "Peaceful reunification" and "One Country,
Two Systems."
</P>
<P>
The meeting, with 50 participants, was held at the Great Hall
of the People's new Hall of Hong Kong, which was used for the
first time since its recent completion.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee and secretary of the
Central Committee's Secretariat, and Qian Qichen, also member of
the Political Bureau and vice-premier, attended the forum.
</P>
<P>
Qian said in his speech that frank discussion and careful study
of Deng's reunification theories are of significance for the
smooth return of Hong Kong to the motherland and for maintaining
its long-term prosperity and stability since July 1.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong's return will be an important step for
China's reunification cause. Afterward, China will follow Deng's
theories in solving the problem of Macao, and eventually to
realize the reunification of the two sides across the Taiwan
Strait.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen said that on the occasion of greeting the Hong
Kong's return to the motherland, studying Deng's reunification
theories is a good way to inspire the Chinese people's patriotic
spirit and advance the country's reform, opening up and
modernization process.
</P>
<P>
"We must unite more closely around the Party central committee
with Jiang Zemin at the core, uphold the banner of Deng's theory
on building socialism with Chinese characteristics and do a good
job of everything, so as to greet the return of Hong Kong and the
15th CPC National Congress," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
