<HEADLINE> Shanghai, Hong Kong Present Hong Kong in VCD </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A video compact disc (VCD) titled
"Hong Kong's Most," featuring 97 wide-ranging aspects of Hong
Kong, was jointly issued here today by Shanghai and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The VCD's publishers said it is a gift dedicated to Hong Kong's
return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
It presents a comprehensive presentation of Hong Kong as the
world's largest port of entrepot trade, the largest shipping and
tourism centers in the world, the third largest financial center,
and having the fourth largest gold market and the eighth largest
stock market.
</P>
<P>
Subjects covered in "Hong Kong's Most" include the economy,
culture, science and technology, education, municipal
administration, history, geology, and social life.
</P>
<P>
All of the material in the VCD was filmed in Hong Kong. Some
segments were borrowed from rare video collections owned by Hong
Kong people. Some of the film is being shown to the public for the
first time on the new disc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
