<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Photo Album on HK Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Hong Kong, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A big photo album on Hong Kong
was published here today.
</P>
<P>
A collection of more than 600 precious documentary photos
depicting the past and present of Hong Kong, the album entitled
"Hong Kong" was co-compiled by Beijing-based Xinhua News Agency
and Hong Kong-based Sino United Publishing (Holdings) Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, a Chinese vice-premier, wrote a foreword for the
album, while Tung Chee-hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, autographed the album's title.
</P>
<P>
In his foreword, the vice-premier recalls the history of how
Hong Kong was seized by Britain and efforts of the Chinese
government to resolve the Hong Kong question.
</P>
<P>
After reviewing the formation of the "one country, two systems"
concept, the Sino-British Joint Declaration and the Basic Law, the
vice-premier says, "The return of Hong Kong to China accords with
the feelings of the people and the general course of events; the
trend of history is irreversible."
</P>
<P>
"Relying on the prosperous development of the motherland and the
industry and ingenuity of the six million local compatriots, Hong
Kong is bound to have an even more splendid future in the 21st
century," he writes.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony marking the publication of the album was held here
this afternoon, drawing several hundred dignitaries including T.K.
Ann, a vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, Zhou Nan, Director of
Hong Kong Branch of Xinhua News Agency, and Tung Chee-hwa.
</P>
<P>
The album serves as a vivid testimony of the history of Hong
Kong, which helps enhance people's pride for and confidence in
their motherland, Zhou Nan said on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The album is a good educational material, Tung Chee-hwa said.
</P>
<P>
The bilingual Chinese and English album will be available both
in Hong Kong and in other parts of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
