<HEADLINE> Central China Province Opens TV &AMP; Radio Digital Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
today launched a 700-km-plus digital microwave network for TV and
radio transmission, which is believed to be the second network of
its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
Jointly built by the province and a US investment company, the
network is able to transmit 32 TV channels and 64 radio channels
as well as other information.
</P>
<P>
