<HEADLINE> Argentina Wins Opening Match in World Youth Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Argentina
won its opening group E match by defeating Hungary 3-0 at the
World Youth Soccer Championships at Kangar on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Mexico whitewashed the United Arab Emirates 5-0
in group F at Johor Baru and Spain edged Japan 2-1 in group D at
Kuantan.
</P>
<P>
In Today's match, Argentina showed a masterly tactical play to
beat Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Bernardo Romeo of Argentina scored the opening in the ninth
minute and Lionel Scaloni added another three minutes before the
break.
</P>
<P>
Roman Riquelme sealed Argentina's superiority five minutes
after the interval.
</P>
<P>
The United Arab Emirates proved no match for the skillful
Mexicans and conceded two goals in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's Eduardo Lillingston scored once in each half and
Carlos Carino, Gerardo Torres and Omar Santacruz netted one goal
each.
</P>
<P>
In their next matches on Friday, Mexico take on Ivory Coast
while the UAE meet England.
</P>
<P>
Spain dominated the Japanese defence from the start and were
rewarded with two goals by Francisco Farinos in the 22nd minute
and Miguel Angulo in the 55th.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese narrowed the margin in the 66th minute through
Atsushi Yanagisawa's penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
Two top teams and four best third-place finishers from the six
groups will advance to the last 16. The final will be played on
July 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
