<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng Inspects Chongqing Municipality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng has
urged local officials and the citizens of China's newest
municipality to make concerted efforts to build a prosperous city.
</P>
<P>
During an inspection tour from June 15 to 18, Li visited
several major enterprises in Chongqing, which was named a
municipality directly under the central government at the Fifth
Session of the National People's Congress held in March.
</P>
<P>
Li said Chongqing faces difficult challenges: successfully
resettling the local people in the Three Gorges reservoir area,
and keeping the economy of the city in step with its overall
development.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of Chongqing, a number of officials
have been sent there from other parts of the country to work. Li
called on both new and existing officials to unite in their
efforts, and be conscientious in their duties.
</P>
<P>
As an old industrial base, Chongqing has been playing a key
role in promoting the development of the national economy. The
current problems in Chongqing can be solved by means of reform and
economic restructuring, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chongqing can develop its chemical industry by
relying on its advantage in natural gas resources. As for the old
enterprises, technological upgrading should be carried out in line
with the market economy, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
