<HEADLINE> Arab Parliamentary Union Condemns US Congressional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Arab Parliamentary Union has
denounced the recent resolution adopted by the U.S. House of
Representatives saying that Jerusalem is the unified capital of
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Damascus-seated Union, in a statement released last night,
described the resolution as flagrant provocation and great
humiliation to hundreds of millions of Muslims and Christians the
world over, and as open violation of UN resolutions on the holy
city.
</P>
<P>
It considered the resolution as anticipating the results of the
final status talks between the Palestinian National Authority and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The statement pointed out that resolution plunges the region
into violence, or rather explosion. Besides, it encourages Israel
to maintain with its aggressive designs against the Arab people,
and to proceed with its settlement policies in the occupied Arab
territories, particularly Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Union called upon the US Administration to abstain from
accepting this unfair and partial resolution. It also called
upon all Arab governments to unify their policies and to take a
collective stance in responding to the that resolution, with a
view to preserving the Arab nature of Jerusalem and implementation
of the related international resolutions. 
</P>
