<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Wins 40 Million Dollar Loan from Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria has secured a
40-million-U.S.-dollar loan from Kuwait for building Sofia
International Airport, according to Kuwaiti officials today.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the grant was reached during Bulgarian
President Petar Stoyanov's three-day visit to Kuwait, which ended
today.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian President said after meeting Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh
Jaber al-Ahmed al-Sabah last night that Kuwait had expressed
readiness to extend the loan, adding that a team from the Kuwaiti
Fund for Arab Economic Development would fly to Sofia for this
purpose in the coming few months.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country considered Kuwait as "its window for
bolstering ties with the other Arab Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC)
states."
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria is seeking to sign the agreement of investment
encouragement and protection with all the GCC states, some of
which have not established diplomatic relations with the eastern
European country.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov, heading a high ranking delegation, arrived in Kuwait
Monday. This is the second time that a Bulgarian head of state
paid visit to Kuwait. Former Bulgarian President Zhelyu Zhelev
visited Kuwait in April 1993.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov called his visit "the start of a new relationship and
cooperation with Kuwait and the entire Gulf Cooperation Council
states." 
</P>
