<HEADLINE> McColgan Quits Track for Marathon Running </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Former world 10,000 meters champion
Liz McColgan of Scotland announced on Wednesday she is to quit the
international track scene to concentrate on marathon running,
according to reports from Glasgow.
</P>
<P>
McColgan announced her intention just a week after undergoing a
back operation and will now not take part in the world athletics
championships in Athens in August.
</P>
<P>
