<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Optimistic About Hong Kong's Stability, Prosperity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen
Manh Cam said today that implementing the "one country, two
systems" principle will ensure the continued stability and
prosperity of Hong Kong and benefit peace and development in the
region.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement released to Xinhua, Cam noted that
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
is an important historic event that marks an end to foreign
colonial rule over Hong Kong for over a century.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam people wish to warmly congratulate the Chinese
people on Hong Kong's return to her motherland, he added.
</P>
<P>
Cam said that Hong Kong has long been one of Vietnam's major
economic partners, with their economic and trade ties developing
even faster in recent years.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May this year, Hong Kong had been the third
largest investor in Vietnam, with a total contracted investment of
3.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Cam expressed the hope that Vietnam's relations with China and
its economic and trade ties with Hong Kong will develop further
after China resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on
July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
