<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila, Muslim Rebels End Low-level Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government and the
secessionist Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) today ended
their fifth round of low-level talks in the southern city of
Cotabato with no major issues resolved.
</P>
<P>
But both sides agreed to meet again on June 28 and 29 to
discuss a government proposal for a general cessation of
hostilities, which would cover the entire island of Mindanao,
according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The issue of repositioning the troops in Buldon Town, the
southern province of Maguindanao, had been temporarily set aside
when the two-day meeting ended.
</P>
<P>
Ghadzali Jaafar, MILF vice-chairman for political affairs,
views the new twist in the negotiation "positively" as a broader
cease-fire could be achieved soon.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the advent of a new proposal, the existing
regional cease-fire in Buldon should continue to be in effect as
this is an official agreement signed earlier by both parties to
prevent future clashes and bloodshed.
</P>
<P>
Jaafar said a government panel had already submitted to MILF
negotiators the proposal on the general cessation issue.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, on the other hand, is set to study its contents to
come up with a counter proposal that would be presented during
their next meeting.
</P>
<P>
But both sides failed to comment on Tuesday's battles between
them, which left 15 MILF rebels and two soldiers dead as the
government troops successfully rescued 43 hostages held by the
rebels Monday.
</P>
<P>
The MILF is a breakaway faction of the former rebel group --
the Moro National Liberation Front (MNLF), which already signed a
peace deal with the government last September. But the MILF was
not included in the peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
The MILF and the smaller Muslim extremist Abu Sayyaf are the
two remaining Muslim rebel groups still fighting the government.
The military estimates the MILF has a membership of nearly 12,000.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
