<HEADLINE> 23 Soldiers Killed in East Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- About 23 Army soldiers were killed
today when government troops on patrol were attacked by a group of
Tamil rebels at Pulmuddai in Eastern Province of Sri Lanka,
according to military sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the troops counterattacked with mortar fire,
causing heavy casualties to the rebels who fled into the near
jungle with their dead and wounded.
</P>
