<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hkhk-HHKSAR PC Makes Historical contributions to HK's Smooth Transition (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In accordance with the method of forming the Selection
Committee, the Preparatory Committee first defined the
qualification of candidates for the Selection Committee from among
applicants of all social strata in Hong Kong and then set forth
the proposed candidates.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, the meeting attended by the Preparatory Committee
chairman and vice-chairmen drew up a list of candidates in
accordance with the votes they had obtained at a rate of 20
percent more than the seats. Finally, the committee
members elected 340 members for the Selection Committee by secret
ballot, which forms the 400-member Selection Committee together
with 26 Hong Kong deputies to the National People's Congress and
34 Hong Kong members of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
After the establishment of the Selection Committee, the
election of the first chief executive of the HKSAR and selection
of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) were placed on the
agenda. following a process of application, qualification
examination, nomination and debate, the first SAR chief executive
was elected by secret ballot on December 11, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Preparatory Committee offered many valuable
suggestions on the formation of the PLC. On December 21 the same
year, the Selection Committee elected a 60-member PLC in Shenzhen,
in south China's Guangdong Province. One month later, Rita Fan was
elected chairwoman of the PLC.
</P>
<P>
To maintain Hong Kong's economic prosperity, the Economic Panel
of the Preparatory Committee studied and set forth a number of
suggestions on major issues concerning the transfer of power in
Hong Kong and its smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
In the field of legislation, the Preparatory Committee studied
specific methods on the implementation of the Nationality Law of
China in Hong Kong and the right of abode and proposed a flexible
and lenient plan in accordance with the Basic Law, the Nationality
Law and a series of policies of the Chinese Government on the
nationality of residents in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
On the principle of basically not changing the laws previously
in force in Hong Kong, the Preparatory Committee has examined the
640 written laws in force in Hong Kong and 1,100 pieces of
subordinate legislation and drew up a proposal on handling the
laws in force in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to the embrace of the motherland is a
joyous event for all people across China. To ensure that all
celebration activities would proceed smoothly, the Preparatory
Committee has defined an outlined framework for the
non-governmental celebration in Hong Kong and promoted the
establishment of the Committee for Activities to Celebrate Hong
Kong's Return to the Motherland by Various Sectors in Hong Kong,
which won support from people of all social strata in Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
