<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Namibian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference(CPPCC) met with Kandy Nehova, Chairman of National
Council of Namibia, and his party here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the Chinese and Namibian people have enjoyed
traditional friendship, and there have been frequent exchanges of
visits between senior leaders of the two countries since the two
forged diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
And economic cooperation between the two sides has been
fruitful, he added.
</P>
<P>
The successful exchange of visits between Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and his Namibian counterpart Sam Nujoma last year have
promoted the bilateral relations, Li said, adding that China
appreciates the Namibian government's "One China" position and its
valuable support to China regarding some major international
issues.
</P>
<P>
On China's domestic situation, Li noted that since new China
was born in 1949, it has scored brilliant achievements, even
though it traveled a tortuous road for a period of time.
</P>
<P>
Both the positive and negative experiences show that the major
task after assuming a position of power is to unite the nation,
stabilize society, develop the economy and improve the people's
living standard, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Nehova said that the Namibian people had established friendly
cooperative ties with the Chinese before its independence, and
this friendship has developed continuously thanks to the joint
efforts of the leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Namibian government and people, Nehova thanked
China's support to Namibia in all aspects.
</P>
<P>
Nehova and his party are here as guests of the CPPCC National
Committee.  
</P>
