<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government is to
establish regular air and road links with the Democratic Republic of
Congo in a bid to explore and promote business ties between the
people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Uganda will also in near future establish railway links via Arua
Town, norhtwestern Uganda, with Democratic Congo.
</P>
<P>
