Democratic Congo as well as other central African countries.
</P>
<P>
The change of government in former Zaire, Kadaga said, was a
pleasant development from which Uganda stands to gain both
economically and from security point of view.
</P>
<P>
She said the new leadership under President Laurent Kabila of
Democratic Congo has identified a new political and economical
policies geared towards promoting cooperation and trade links in
the Great Lakes region.
</P>
<P>
