<HEADLINE> 27 Drug Dealers Executed in Kunming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 27 drug dealers were
executed and 1,000 kilograms of heroin was burned in Kunming,
capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, after local People's
Court pronounced judgement today.
</P>
<P>
Yang Jianqiang, secretary of the city's Communist Party
Committee, said concerted efforts are needed to fight against
illicit drugs and that the fight should not end until illegal drug
deals are eradicated.
</P>
<P>
Su Miaozhi, Gong Dehui, Li Zukuan and Lin Yanqi were caught
with 15.99 kilograms of heroin on the way from Kunming to Qujing
City on January 13, 1995.
</P>
<P>
Duan Qingfeng was captured with 3.83 kilograms of heroin when
Duan sold it at home on July 25, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province, bordering on Vietnam, Laos and Myanmar, has
become a frontline of China's battles against domestic and
overseas drug traffickers. 
</P>
