<HEADLINE> Chairman and Vice-Chairpersons of Top Legislature Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The 26th session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee will be held
from June 27 to July 3.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made here today by a meeting presided by NPC
Standing Committee Member Qiao Shi and attended by the committee's
vice-chairpersons. The agenda of the upcoming session was also
approved at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
It was announced in today's meeting that the committee members
will discuss the draft namelist of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) Basic Law Committee under the NPC
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The group will deliberate on three motions involving some of
China's national laws to be applied in Hong Kong, the completion
of work of the Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong SAR, and
the timeframe for electing the deputies of county-level people's
congresses.
</P>
<P>
The session will examine drafts or motions related to highways,
animal quarantine, advanced education and flood control efforts.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the group will discuss reports from the State
Council about the central government's final accounts for 1996,
and about the implementation of the budgets of the central
government for 1996. 
</P>
