<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Russian swimmers for the
European championships in Seville in August may be disrupted by a
cash shortage, according to Wednesday's Sport Express newspaper.
</P>
<P>
"The Russian Olympic Committee and swimming federation failed
to get enough money for the national team to train in a
coordinated way," the Newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Many national stars have been forced to train separately in
their local swimming centers in Volgograd, Samara or Saint
Petersburg.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 team members, including Denis Pankratov, a double
gold-medallist in the 1996 Olympic Games butterfly competition,
will leave for Portugal soon for training, but the trip will be
personally funded by the team's chief coach Viktor Avdiyenko.
