<HEADLINE> Shanghai Petrochemical Firm Steps up Technical Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Petrochemical Co. Ltd is
carrying out three major technical upgrading programs that will
enable the company to become China's biggest producer of ethylene,
polypropylene fiber, and acrylic fiber when finished.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of share holders of the company today,
Wang Jiming, chairman of the board, briefed participants on the
company's performance and the company's development plan.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, the company's project of enlarging its
current 300,000-ton ethylene production equipment into a facility
with a production capacity of 400,000 tons will be finished in
1998.
</P>
<P>
By then, the company's ethylene production capacity will be
improved from present 450,000 tons to 550,000 tons, accounting for
one sixth of the country's total output.
</P>
<P>
In addition to conducting large-scale technical upgrading, the
company has also enlarged its production capacity of hot-selling
products and improved technical content of products, in a bid to
enhance the company's competitiveness on the market, said Wang.
</P>
<P>
Development of in-depth processing service for the
petrochemical industry and refined chemicals will be the focus of
the company's technical upgrading, said Wang.
</P>
<P>
The central Chinese government has listed the petrochemical
industry as one of the country's development priorities from 1996
to the year of 2010.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Municipality has also treated development of in-depth
processing service of the petrochemical industry as a new economic
powerhouse and has decided to build a new chemical industrial zone
around the company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
