<HEADLINE> 430 Ancient Tombs Unearthed in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 430 tombs dating back to
the Shang (16-11th Century BC), Tang (618-907), and the Song
(960-1279) dynasties have been excavated at a construction site in
Anyang city in central China's Henan province.
</P>
<P>
Ten porcelain kilns from the Song Dynasty were also unearthed
at the site, where a local iron and steel complex is to build an
100-ton electronic furnace.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,100 relics, including inscribed ritual bronze ware,
have been found in the place.  
</P>
