<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The port city of Dalian in
northeast China is speeding up construction of a 123.5-km-long
highway, to stimulate the economic development of its suburban
areas.
</P>
<P>
The highway, called "Huanghai" road starts from Zhuanghe Town
in the east, and ends at the No. Five Road of the Dalian Economic
Development Zone in the west.
</P>
<P>
The highway will connect most of the large and medium-sized
enterprises with four of the city's ports.
</P>
<P>
"This road will help develop the rural economy, and integrate
the countryside with the urban areas of the city," a local
official said.
</P>
<P>
The finished highway will open to traffic on October 1, 1998.
