<HEADLINE> Hebei to Increase Agricultural Cooperation with Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has recently signed agreements with five states of the European
Union to increase cooperation in agriculture in the next decade.
</P>
<P>
The five European countries are France, Italy, Spain, Belgium,
and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreements, extensive cooperation and exchange
will be done between Hebei and the five states in agricultural
technology, information, and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The five states will set up a demonstration project for Hebei,
to teach and spread Europe's agricultural production methods and
social service system.
</P>
<P>
The province will dispatch agricultural administration
personnel and technicians to Europe to study the advanced
technology and management expertise from the five countries.
</P>
<P>
The province will introduce newly developed seeds and
agricultural machineries to improve local agricultural production
capacity and the processing industry of sideline products.
</P>
<P>
An information network will be built in the province to collect
timely information on economic cooperation and overseas investment
in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The agreements also say that the two sides will set up joint
ventures in Hebei to diversify local agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
The agreements was signed between the provincial government of
Hebei and a delegation from the five states to investigate local
agriculture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
