LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- British boxer Chris Henry was in
critical condition here on Wednesday following his collapse in
Tuesday's bout.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old was in "critical but stable" condition in a
hospital in northeast London, the hospital's spokesman said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Henry was bleeding from the mouth after receiving blows from
his opponent Dominic Nevas in the 10th round of his defence of
southern England cruiserweight title.
</P>
<P>
He then crashed into the ropes and almost went down as referee
Tony Walker stopped the fight.
</P>
<P>
The physician on duty at the site confirmed that Henry might
have brain injury before he was carried out of the ring on
strechers and sent to hospital. 
</P>
