<HEADLINE> Over 70 Percent of Disabled People in China Have Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 70 percent of the
disabled in China are employed, according to the China Disabled
Persons Federation.
</P>
<P>
To help employ disabled persons, China reduces taxation of
factories in which disabled employees are the majority and
provides low-interest loans to them. The country's favorable
policies to the factories have increased the number of these
enterprises to more than 60,000, which earn over 500 million US
dollars in export every year.
</P>
<P>
The country has some 1,200 agencies providing technical
training and job information to the disabled, and more than 5,000
people are devoted to this work in China.
</P>
<P>
The country's 23 province-level areas has stipulated that the
rate of disabled employees in each firm should reach from 1.5 to
two percent.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in urban areas, 83 percent of the disabled
have jobs. More than 900,000 disabled people are working in
private factories or have become private businessmen themselves.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
