<HEADLINE> Ancient Town Ruins Found in Taklimakan Desert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Ruins of a more than 2,100-year old
ancient town have been discovered in the center of Taklimakan
Desert in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 historical relics including pottery, stone,
wooden, bronze and iron articles, and many animal bones and
grains, have also been unearthed in the 330 by 270 m town and six
ancient tombs around it.
</P>
<P>
The ruins were discovered by three experts from a Sino-French
archaeological research team which started exploration and
excavation in 1993.
</P>
<P>
One of the experts said that most of the buildings in the town
was covered under the sand, only a 473-meter town wall and two
city gates remain standing on the desert. 
</P>
