<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- French soccer international Patrice
Loko is facing a suspended eight-month sentence on charges of
indecent exposure and damaging property on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A state prosecutor asked a court on Wednesday to give the
27-year-old Paris-Saint-Germain forward the sentence to punish him
for what French media called "crazy night" two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Loko, who was capped for France 26 times, kicked two cars
outside a Paris nightclub, spat in the face of the police officer
who arrested him and urinated in public.
</P>
<P>
Loko, whose two goals against Liverpool in April qualified his
club Paris Saint Germain for the European Cup Winners Cup Final,
told the court he deserved to be punished.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor asked the court to order Loko to compensate
victims and submit to regular medical and psychiatric tests. The
court will give its verdict at a later date. 
