<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Economy Keeps Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese economy maintained
steady growth in May, with industrial production growing and
inflation decreasing.
</P>
<P>
According to a report which was made public here today by the
State Statistics Bureau, China had an added value of 178 billion
yuan in industrial production in May, an increase of 11.9 percent
over same month last year, and that light industry enjoyed a
slightly bigger growth rate than heavy industry.
</P>
<P>
A survey on 370,000 industrial enterprises nationwide shows
that these enterprises made a total profit of 29.3 billion yuan in
the January-April period, 39.2 percent up over the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
The state sector made a profit of 2.07 billion yuan during
these four months, while the sector suffered a loss in the first
quarter, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China invested 356.3 billion yuan on fixed
assets during the January-May period, 14 percent more than the
corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
China's real estate investment for the first time showed a
decrease in the recent few years. Total investment on real estate
was 65.1 billion yuan in May, 2.9 percent less than the same month
last year.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China's retail sales volume rose 13
percent, or 12.2 percent in real terms, to 210.8 billion yuan in
May.
</P>
<P>
During the period of January to May, China exported 65.5
billion yuan-worth of goods, a rise of 26.4 percent over the same
period last year. The country's import dropped by 1.2 percent to
51.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
China enjoyed a surplus of 13.9 billion US dollars; at the same
period last year, China had a trade deficit of 490 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China's retail price index rose by two
percent in January-May period on an annual basis while its
consumer price index rose by 4.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
