<HEADLINE> Quadruplets In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Four baby boys born in the
Shandong Provincial Hospital on May 27 became the newest addition
to China's quadruplets, according to "Beijing Evening News".
</P>
<P>
They make up one of five sets of quadruplets born in China this
year, bringing the number of sets to 38. Two boys and two girls
were born in Taiwan on February 27, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The chance of giving birth to quadruplets is one in more than
700,000, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
The oldest quadruplets in China are four 35-year-old daughters
living in Shanghai. There are six sets in Taiwan and Hong Kong,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
On May 12, eleven quadruplet families had a big gathering in
Shanghai, the first party of its kind in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
