<HEADLINE> One-Third S.Africans Have Heartburn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- One third of all South Africans
suffer from heartburn and acid indigestion caused by bad eating
habits, excessive alcohol consumption and stressful lifestyle, said a
medical survey here today.
</P>
<P>
The foundings show that six percent of the survey
respondents had symptoms that could indicate gastric ulcers and
cardiovascular problems.
</P>
<P>
The symptoms include a burning sensation radiating up to the
ears, buring pain behind the breastbone which worsens with exercise,
buring or pain radiating down the arms, sometimes to the little
fingers, the feeling that something is stuck in one's throat and
diffculty in swallowing.
</P>
<P>
The survey also showed that 17 percent of the sample had very poor
eating and drinking habits, which caused their discomfort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
