<HEADLINE> Express Mail Service More Rapid Between Shanghai, HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Mail between Shanghai and Hong
Kong through Express Mail Service (EMS) will reach the destination
the next day after they are posted, for a two-month period from
mid-June to August.
</P>
<P>
This is the result of a joint action made by the
Directorate-General of Posts under the Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications and the Hong Kong Post Office.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, mail sent to Hong Kong via EMS during the period
will have a 30 percent cut in fee. But, the fee for added weight
will not change.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's postal service has set up special counters in the
downtown area to collect mails to be sent through EMS to Hong
Kong.  
</P>
