<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Former US Secretary of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
here today with former US Secretary of State Henry Kissinger.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation for Dr. Kissinger's efforts in
the past years for safeguarding and promoting the development of
Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there are important common interests between China
and the US, Jiang recalled his meeting with US President Bill
Clinton last year in Manila, saying that during the meeting, both
sides agreed that they would seek common ground while reserving
differences and make joint efforts to establish a stable and
healthy Sino-US relationship for the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang continued that recently, bilateral relations have
basically maintained the upward momentum which emerged in the
latter half of last year.
</P>
<P>
To seize the opportunity to push bilateral relations to a new
high requires not only the joint efforts from the two governments,
but also the active promotion of people of insight of various
circles, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Kissinger would employ his influence
and continue to play an active role in promoting the further
improvement and development of Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that there are only 13 days left before China
resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, and expressed
his confidence in Hong Kong's stable transition and smooth
handover.
</P>
<P>
To guarantee a long-term prosperity and stability in Hong Kong
is not only in the interest of China itself, but also conducive to
all the countries including the US, Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Kissinger said that US-China relationship is the most
important bilateral relationship in the current world, and that
the maintenance of a sound and stable relationship between the two
countries is not only conducive to world peace and stability, but
will also have an influence on the direction of the world in the
next century.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger told Jiang that he, as many US people, is expecting
Jiang's state visit to the US scheduled in autumn this year, and
expressed the belief that this important visit will bring
bilateral relations into a new stage.
</P>
<P>
He said he is convinced that Hong Kong will keep its prosperity
and stability after its return.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign
Affairs Office of the State Council, and Mei Zhaorong, president
of the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger and his party are here as guest of the institute.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
