<HEADLINE> Nigeria Spends More on Water Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is spending about 15.4
billion Naira (about 181 million U.S. dollars) on various water
supply projects nationwide, the " Guardian" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Head of State, General Sani Abacha said that his
administration is determined to provide potable water for every
Nigerian.
</P>
<P>
Abacha made the remarks at the national conference on water
sector reform held a few day ago in Abuja. He said Nigeria's
Petroleum Trust Fund (PTF) is using 22 percent of its resources
on water projects.
</P>
<P>
PTF was set up in 1994 with an aim, among others,to divert the
country's huge income from oil exports to health, education, road
and other infrastructure sectors.
</P>
<P>
Its Chairman, former Head of State Muhammudu Buhari said PTF
has received 70 billion Naira (about 824 million dollars) in the
past three years.
</P>
<P>
Water Resources Minister Alhaji Jibril Aliyu Yelwa has noted
that the lack of access to water and sanitation " is at the heart
of poverty trap and social-economic degradation". 
</P>
</TEXT>
