<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sweden Fails to Achieve Environment Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Sweden has failed to achieve the
target of lowering nitrogen emissions by 50 percent between 1985
and 1995, a government report said.
</P>
<P>
"This target has not been achieved. The emissions have declined
by 20 percent so far," the report by the National Environment
Protection Board (NEPB) said.
</P>
<P>
Pollution caused by nitrogen emissions in inland water and
densely populated areas have affected the coastal areas much more
than was previously thought, the report.
</P>
<P>
The most affected areas are the Maelar region around Stockholm
and along parts of Sweden's west coast.
</P>
<P>
The board has proposed vigorous efforts in fullfuling Sweden's
commitments in environment protection.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish government will study the NEPB report and
proposals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
