<HEADLINE> S. Korea Predicts Normal Business With Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will continue to serve as
the financial hub of East Asia in the coming century after it
returns to China, said an official of the South Korean Ministry of
Finance and Economy (MOFE).
</P>
<P>
South Korean businesses in Hong Kong remain unchanged with 10
days away from the territory's return to China, and they won't be
affected by the transfer of power in the territory since China
pledges to keep the policy of "one country, two systems" to
guarantee Hong Kong's status as an international financial hub,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
Most of South Korean banks operating in Hong Kong forecast
little change in business after Hong Kong returns to China,
according to a survey conducted by the MOFE. 
</P>
