<HEADLINE> Share Prices Index Declines On Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed in
dull trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index declined sharply by 19.12 points to close
at 1985.14 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume remained thin at 85.38 million units,
worth 266.68 million Singapore dollars (about 186.49 million US
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 160 to 128, while 337
other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
HTP Holdings was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 3.9 million units. It was followed by
Westmont Land which had 3.25 million shares traded. The Overseas
Union Bank (OUB) Foreign was next with 2.92 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by one Singapore dollar to finish at 25.2
dollars. Samanda Holdings gained 90 cents to end at 11.3 Singapore
dollars, while Clipsal closed 30 cents higher at 3.9 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, UMW was the biggest loser as it declined by 95
cents to end at 7.1 dollars. Alex Holdings fell by 70 cents to
close at 2.8 dollars, while City Developments and the Singapore
Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign dropped by 60 cents each to finish at
13.1 and 28 Singapore dollars respectively.  
</P>
