Tuesday. Among the 5,600 jobs to be reduced as was planned by the
1997 budget law, 5,000 would be from the sector of national
education and should be implemented from September.
</P>
<P>
-- Since the establishment of a leftist government that was
joined by the Greens, several great projects of public
infrastructures have been frozen in France. Experts accused the
Minister of Environment and Territory Management Dominique Voynet,
who is head of the Greens, of adopting a totally negative attitude
toward public infrastructures, although the number of their projects
has been experiencing a free fall for several years. 
