<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Return Enhances Patriotic Sentiments of Chinese Servicemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) and the Armed Police Force, in line with the
instruction of the Chinese Communist Party's Central Committee and
the Central Military Commission, have carried out various
educational activities centering on the return of Hong Kong to its
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Under the unified arrangement by the General Political
Department of the PLA, these activities are aimed at boosting the
national dignity, confidence, and sense of pride among the
officers and men of the army and the armed police force and
enhancing their sense of duty for making contributions to the
reunification of the motherland and revitalization of the nation.
</P>
<P>
The three general departments of the PLA, namely Headquarters
of the General Staff, the General Political Department, and the
General Logistics Department, have arranged the study on the
expositions by Deng Xiaoping on the Hong Kong issue as well as the
important speeches given by President Jiang Zemin on patriotism.
</P>
<P>
Through the study, the officers and men of the three general
departments have deepened their understanding of the great concept
of "One Country, Two Systems" and the Party Central Committee's
policies related to the Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
By organizing visits to the sites of historical importance
nearby their barracks, the forces of the Guangzhou, Shenyang, and
Nanjing Military Area Commands have conducted various educational
activities for their servicemen with the objective to enhance
their patriotic sentiments.
</P>
<P>
Through book-readings and speaking contests on the "One
Country, Two Systems" concept, the PLA air force have learned the
historic contributions made by the Chinese Communist Party to the
country's independence and revitalization.
</P>
<P>
By launching a large scale signature drive, the naval force has
taught its officers and men the lesson how China had suffered over
the past century due to the lack of strong naval defense.
</P>
<P>
The University of National Defense and the Military Academy of
Sciences have held seminars on the Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
Most of these activities took the study of the Basic Law and
the Law Concerning Stationing Troops to the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (the Garrison Law) and other related laws as
their main contents.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou and Chengdu Military Area Commands have organized
the study among the officers and men on the laws related to the
Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
The Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense and the Second Artillery Force have organized quizzes on
the Basic Law and the Garrison Law.
</P>
<P>
The Jinan Military Area Command has combined the study of the
Basic Law and the Garrison Law with that of the National Defense
Law and have further boosted the patriotic sentiments of its
officers and men.
</P>
<P>
In order to create a good social environment for the return of
Hong Kong, the Guangdong Provincial Military Command has
encouraged its officers and soldiers to carry out their duties in
a more civilized way and in accordance with the law and have
strengthened their enforcement of the law.
</P>
<P>
Units of the armed police force stationed along the
Beijing-Kowloon Railway line have mobilized a special group to
ensure the railway's smooth operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Funds Flow To Hainan Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Hainan Island in south China is
still a favorite destination for investment from Hong Kong. Every
year, millions of dollars are flowing into this island that has
become the largest special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
Funds from Hong Kong account for the biggest share of overseas
investment in the island, totalling 2.5 billion US dollars so far.
</P>
<P>
Investment from Hong Kong still flows into Hainan at a rate of
125.52 million US dollars per year.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, Hong Kong business
people opened 29 joint ventures in Hainan, with a total contract
value of 93 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
As one of the few unpolluted land plots designated by the
United Nations, Hainan has drawn some of the largest real estate
projects from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The 30-square-kilometer Yangpu Development Area is an
investment coup for Kumagai Gumi (H.K.) Ltd. After pumping five
billion Hong Kong dollars into the real estate joint ventures in
China in the past four years, the developer is luring
construction projects into the area.
</P>
<P>
C. P. Yu, managing director and deputy-chairman of Kumagai
Gumi, said that the company is striving to turn an ambitious
blueprint into reality, to turn Yangpu into another Hong Kong as
late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping had envisioned.
</P>
<P>
Hainan, the southern-most province of China, has been
attractive to overseas developers for its preferential policy on
large-scale land development projects.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong-Macao International Investment Company from Hong
Kong channeled 75 million US dollars into the construction of a
large-scale power plant near Haikou, capital city of the island
province. The 250,000-kilowatt power plant generates the bulk of
the electricity needed by the whole island.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong funds have fueled real estate and infrastructure
development in Hainan in the past ten years, making Hong Kong the
top investor in the island. Now funds are re-channeled to other
fields of growth, such as high technology and environment.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong-Macao Industrial Development Area, one of the
earliest set up by Hong Kong investors on the island, has shifted
its industrial focal point from labor-intensive manufacturing
industries to fund- and technology-intensive industries, such as
biological engineering, precision instruments, and chemicals.
</P>
<P>
New projects set up in the area include a 35-million-US-dollar
glassware factory and a 800-million-yuan (96-million-US-dollar)
polyester plant.
</P>
<P>
A tropical botanic garden is taking shape in Hainan under the
sponsorship of a Hong Kong company. The chairman of the company
said that he will build the haven of rare tropic plants into a
"project with the image of the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
As the return of Hong Kong to the motherland is approaching,
Hainan is planning to tap its human and natural resources more
fully so as to draw more funds, technology, and talents from Hong
Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "China's Foreign Affairs" (1997 edition) Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 edition of "China's
Foreign Affairs", which elaborates China's views on the
international situation and its diplomatic activities of the
previous year, was published by the World Knowledge Publishing
House recently.
</P>
<P>
This year's edition, compiled by the Policies Research Office
of China's Foreign Ministry, records the development and change of
relations between China and all other countries, and international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The book described the international situation in 1996 as
remaining relaxed in general, but many destablizing and uncertain
factors still existed; the relations between big countries
underwent major and profound readjustments; a global multi-polar
pattern further developed; economic elements played an increasing
role in the international relations, while elements of
geopolitics, military security, and ideology were conspicuous; the
situation in some regional hotspots fluctuated, and it was complex
and changeable; regional and global economic cooperation was
enhanced, competition was more intense, some positive changes took
place in the south-north relations.
</P>
<P>
On China's diplomatic activities in 1996, it says, China
observed its independent foreign policy for peace and took a
positive attitude toward enhancing its good-neighborly relations
of friendship with neighboring countries, noting that friendship
and cooperation between China and other developing nations were
promoted obviously, while extensively improving its relations and
enhancing mutually-beneficial cooperation with Western countries.
</P>
<P>
It also says that China engaged in last year's diplomatic work
in a comprehensive and multi-faceted manner, pointing out that
Chinese leaders visited 36 countries in five continents, and some
40 foreign state and government leaders visited China, enhancing
mutual understanding and friendly cooperation between China and
other countries.
</P>
<P>
China continued to play a positive role in multilateral
activities and major international affairs, and participated in
diplomatic activities of both the United Nations and regional
organizations in a wide range of areas, contributing to world
peace and common development, it says.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government firmly safeguarded state sovereignty,
territorial integrity, and national dignity in 1996, struggled
against any acts of interference in China's internal affairs, and
pushed ahead the cause for the reunification of the motherland,
according to the new edition.
</P>
<P>
The 700,000-plus-character edition summarizes the international
situation, China's relations with other countries and
international organizations and its activities in treaty,
legislative, and consular affairs.
</P>
<P>
The appendix to the book includes significant speeches made by
Chinese leaders on diplomatic issues and organizations of China's
Foreign Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
