<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Future HK Government to Work for Proper Housing for All </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The future Hong Kong government
will solve the housing problem in this heavily populated city in a
"fair and open" manner.
</P>
<P>
With housing listed among the top concerns of local residents,
Dominic S. W. Wong, Secretary for Housing, said that the future
Hong Kong government will have a great deal to do to provide
proper housing for all local residents.
</P>
<P>
Wong reveals a housing construction plan for the 1995-2001
period.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the housing branch of the government
will build 510,000 housing units during that period, including
316,000 public housing units and 195,000 units for sale at market
prices to individuals.
</P>
<P>
Wong said the government will provide sufficient land and
proper infrastructure to encourage private real estate developers
to participate in undertaking public housing projects, and retain
the current policy on low-income families, namely, supply them
with high-quality and low-rent apartments.
</P>
<P>
He said that over the next few months the government will
formulate a long-term housing development strategy which will
take the suggestions of local residents into consideration.
</P>
<P>
The 55-year-old secretary has been a public servant for 35
years, and the Secretary for Housing for two-plus years.
</P>
<P>
According to Wong, Hong Kong started to build public housing in
the 1950s, and about 40 percent of Hong Kong residents live in
such housing units whose rents account for about nine percent of
the average income of local tenants.
</P>
<P>
He added another 10 percent of Hong Kong residents live in
housing units they have bought at discount prices, with government
subsidies.
</P>
<P>
Wong is fond of sports, including swimming and badminton, often
takes part in Cantonese Opera and singing performances, and
donates money for charities. He has two sons and one daughter, all
of whom are at school. His wife lends him a great helping hand to
him in his work and family life.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
