<HEADLINE> East China Province Highlights Legal Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui province has been
making a greater effort in increase knowledge of the law among its
citizens.
</P>
<P>
The province has gotten 33.5 million people involved in its
legal awareness drive, 14.2 million people taking tests on the
law, and 90 percent of them passing.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 provincial officials and 250,000 cadres have
also attended a series of lectures on the law.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 700 legal consultants in government
departments in the province, and more than 70,000 administrative
law staff members with certificates.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the province has developed some 200 codes and
regulations, and according to a recent survey, more than 20,000
disputes among people have been prevented from intensifying,
thanks to the legal education drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
