<HEADLINE> Ancient Bronze Plate Returns to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong industrialist has
recently donated a unique 2,800-year-old bronze plate to the
Shanghai Museum.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhaofu (Chinese phonetic alphabet), chairman of the board
of the Sun Group Co.Ltd, spent a large amount of money acquiring the
ancient object, which measures 18cm in height and 45cm in diameter.
</P>
<P>
In its center there is a design of a crowned-bird, surrounded
by four swimming fish. On the rim are four crown-less birds
separated by four squatting frogs.
</P>
<P>
On the inside wall are engraved with thirty-two Chinese
characters, indicating that it was made by a noble for his wife.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists call it a national treasure because of its age,
unique shape, and exquisite designs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
