<HEADLINE> Beijing Dressing Up For Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Banners, flowers, lamps, lanterns,
and scrolls now fill Beijing with a festive atmosphere of
celebration for Hong Kong's return to the motherland in 13 days.
</P>
<P>
According to a municipal government source, the capital will be
decorated with 100,000 banners and 800,000 pots of
flowers. Tian'anmen Square in the heart of the city will have 97
red lanterns and colorful banners and flowers.
</P>
<P>
A "Beijing People Welcome Hong Kong's Return Soiree" will be
held on Tian'anmen Square on the evening of June 30, when a big
lamp will be put up on the south side of the Square, and three
large TV screens will be installed on the Square so that people
can watch the Handover and Swearing-in Ceremonies.
</P>
<P>
The General Office of the Beijing Municipal Government today
asked departments and various non-governmental organizations to
display the national flag during the celebration period.
</P>
<P>
Along Chang'an Avenue there will be banners and neon lamps up
in trees and on buildings. Large-character scrolls will be hung up
on tall buildings, and flowers will be placed in front of the
gates of every unit on the Avenue.
</P>
<P>
At night, all lamps along the Avenue will be lit, and at
Fuxingmen and Jianguomen, two major crossroads, there will be
rainbow-shaped gates.
</P>
<P>
On the evening of July 1, a party for people from all walks of
life will be held in the capital in the Workers' Stadium. Red
lanterns will be hung on the platform, and banners, scrolls, and
flowers will be everywhere in the stadium.
</P>
<P>
At other places, like the Capital Airport, Beijing Railway
Station, Beijing West Railway Station, major parks, and 255 major
streets in Beijing there will also be banners, flowers, scrolls,
balloons, lamps, and pictures.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
