<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blacks: Main Force in S.African Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking in the defense vote debate in National Assembly,
Kasrils said that the SANDF was becoming increasingly representative
of all South Africans.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, fewer than five percent of all officers in South Africa
were black, and there were no black generals. Since then, 14 black
generals had been appointed and the deputy chief of the SANDF,
Lieut-General Sipiwe Nyanda was black.
</P>
<P>
The overall composition of the SANDF was 56 percent African, 12
percent colored, 31 percent white and one percent Indian.
</P>
<P>
More than 11 percent of soldiers were women, the highest percentage
in the world, Kasrils said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
