<HEADLINE> Shell to Invest 5 Billion US Dollars in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Anglo-Dutch multinational,
Shell, plans to invest 5 billion US dollars in India in the coming
years to set up an oil refinery and an import terminal for
liquefied natural gas (LNG) and take up commercial exploitation of
oil wells in the country, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Shell has completed the first phase of its maiden onshore oil
exploration in India and the work on the second phase is in
progress. Shell's first import terminal for LPG in Maharashtra
State in south western India has already become operational and
the second one in Gurajat State in southern India will be
commissioned in December this year and the third one in Andhra
Pradesh will come on stream next year.
</P>
<P>
Shell's proposed refinery in Uttar Pradesh in northern India
will be a stand-alone project and is not tied in any way with the
success of its onshore oil exploration venture in Rajasthan State
near the capital.  
