<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Meets Brunei Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China is pleased to see that the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) has made new
progress in its integration process, said Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen here today during a meeting with Her
Royal Highness Princess Hajah Masna, ambassador-at-large of Brunei.
</P>
<P>
Qian said China supports the new positive development, which is
beneficial to the maintenance and promotion of regional peace and
development.
</P>
<P>
China and Brunei share a long history of friendship, he said,
adding that since the forging of diplomatic ties six years ago,
the two countries have seen a smooth development in bilateral
cooperation in all areas and conducted sound coordination in
regional and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to enhance its relations with Brunei on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to China-ASEAN relations, he
said and expressed his expectation to meet and exchange views with
the foreign ministers from all ASEAN countries this July on
regional issues and relations between China and ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Princess Masna conveyed the regards from Brunei Foreign Minister
Pengiran Muda Mohamad Bolkiah to Qian. She said Brunei and China
share a friendly relationship and there are no problems demanding
prompt solution between both sides.
</P>
<P>
Brunei is satisfied with the increasing exchanges of high-level
visits, growing bilateral trade and economic cooperation, and good
momentum of cultural exchanges and cooperation between the two
countries, she noted.
</P>
<P>
The Princess stressed ASEAN places great importance on its
cooperation of friendship with China and highly appreciates
China's positive contributions to the ASEAN's development.
</P>
<P>
She said Brunei will as always make every effort to support
China's entry into the World Trade Organization at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Princess Masna and her party arrived in Beijing yesterday to
attend this year's consultation between the two foreign ministries
at the invitation of Chinese vice foreign minister Tang Jiaxuan.
</P>
<P>
Tang and Princess Masna consulted on bilateral relations,
China-ASEAN relations, and other issues of common concern. Both
sides reached a consensus on expanding exchanges and cooperation
in trade and economy, culture, sports, and tourism. 
</P>
