<HEADLINE> Rural Shanghai Citizens Applaud Pension System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The nuclear family may become a
rarer phenomenon in rural parts of Shanghai, as some people
gradually turn to an old-age pension system rather than continuing
to rely on their offspring, especially sons, for a living.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is a pioneer in China's rural old-age pension system,
and already has it in all its rural areas, along with a social
security net.
</P>
<P>
According to the census, there are 1.2 million households in
rural parts of Shanghai, or 82 percent of the rural people in need
of insurance. It involves a total of 930 million yuan in premiums.
</P>
<P>
Most of the rural Shanghai residents applaud the old-age
pension system, and people are gradually getting used to the idea
of escaping the traditional notion of raising sons to secure their
lives in old age, according to a survey.
</P>
<P>
But experts say that the rapid income growth of rural Shanghai
citizens is another major factor behind the increasing number of
participants in the rural pension system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
