<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian  Businessman  By Zhao Jinchuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will continue to be
prosperous and its future will become brighter after its return to
China, Sukamdani S. Gitosardjono, president of the Association of
Indonesia-China Economic, Social and Cultural Cooperation, said
here today.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Sukamdani, a leading
Indonesian businessman, said Hong Kong will remain an important
free port, an international financial center, a trade center and a
tourist center after China resumes its exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
"With the return of Hong Kong to China, China will get stronger
economically in the Asia and Pacific region," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Sukamdani, an old friend of the Chinese people, said the return
of Hong Kong to the motherland will be of great significance.
</P>
<P>
He said the "one country, two systems" principle proposed by
Deng Xiaoping is a "great concept" in seeking the best possible
solution of the Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
"The concept is excellent in the framework of the peaceful
reunification of China," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he firmly believed what the Chinese government has
promised -- the laws currently in force in Hong Kong and its
current social and economic systems will remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
"In may opinion, there will be no change of Hong Kong's
international financial and trade positions after its return to
China, as long as its economy will continue to be based on the
open, free and market economy," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He was also convinced that China will certainly be able to keep
the stability and prosperity in Hong Kong in the future.
</P>
<P>
On Sino-Indonesian relations after Hong Kong's return to China,
Sukamdani said the prospects for such ties, especially in economic
and trade fields, will be better and more promising than ever
before.
</P>
<P>
"Indonesia and China are two big countries in the Asia-Pacific
region who need to cooperate with each other for promoting their
international trade and further developing their national
economies for achieving welfare and prosperity for their
respective people," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
