<HEADLINE> Technical Training Stepped up in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- One out of every twelve people
in Guangzhou, the capital of Guangdong province in south China,
has received some form of technical training
</P>
<P>
The number of trained personnel in the city is now more than
500,000. Without technical training, people are finding it more
and more difficult to get a satisfactory job. As a result, making
better use of their spare time by turning to study is now in vogue
in Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
One survey has shown that more than 30 percent of the city's
employees receive over 50 hours of technical training every year.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the number of people flooding Guangzhou from
other parts of China has played an important part in its
development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
