Another plan is to try to tighten the Helms-Burton Act to
frighten away foreign investment from the island.
</P>
<P>
Cuba has sent representatives to the United Nations and to the
World Trade Organization to explain the new threats against Cubans.
</P>
<P>
Cuban Vice President Carlos Lage, Congressional President
Ricardo Alarcon and Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina have also
denounced Washington's schemes against Cuba on visits to various
countries.
</P>
<P>
