<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Postpones Reforms Until Eastward Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMSTERDAM, June 18 (Xinhua) -- European Union leaders agreed
Tuesday night to postpone internal reforms until the bloc's
expansion into eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the 15 member countries failed to reach agreement on
the formula of a new vote distribution in the EU's Council of
Ministers.
</P>
<P>
This fundamental disagreement prevented EU leader from reaching
a compromise on two related issues: the trimming of the European
Commission (EC), the EU's executive body, and the extension of
decision-making in the Council of Ministers through a majority
instead of a unanimous vote.
</P>
<P>
The leaders agreed to limit the number of EC members to one per
state when the EU is expanded to accept more countries early next
century.
</P>
<P>
But they have yet to agree on the number of votes which will
correspond to each member state in the Council of Ministers, and
how this will be done.
</P>
<P>
The alternative being considered is a vote distribution or a
new system called "double majority", which would take into account
the population of each member state.
</P>
<P>
But EU leaders compromised to add into a new treaty a call for
the 15-nation bloc to develop closer relations with the Western
European Union (WEU), but with an eye only for the "possibility"
of an eventual merger.
</P>
<P>
Most of the bloc -- led by France and Germany -- had wanted to
bring the WEU fully into the Union in order to develop a European
defense structure alongside the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO).
</P>
<P>
But Britain -- supported for different reasons by Denmark,
Sweden, Finland, Austria and Ireland -- had argued against the
move, saying it would undermine NATO's position.
</P>
<P>
It was also decided by the leaders that the power of the
European Commission President would be reinforced upon admission
of a new country to the EU, said a spokesman of the Dutch EU
presidency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
