<HEADLINE> Bounced Checks Rise in Northeastern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Bounced checks in northeastern
Thailand increased as the country is undergoing an economic
slowdown, the Bank of Thailand said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The checks unpaid amounted to 3.9 billion baht (156 million US
dollars), accounting for 37.9 percent of the total issued in the
region, the Thai central bank's northeastern regional office said.
</P>
<P>
The checks were rejected by banks as the issuers failed to meet
their obligations on a monthly base, the office said.
</P>
<P>
Bounced checks soared in the region compared with 1994 before
the country's economy began its downward trend. The problems have
promoted businesses in the region to demand more cash payment,
which has affected the business climate in general.  
</P>
</TEXT>
