<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China is giving more
opportunities in issuing stocks to key enterprises in basic
industries such as energy, transportation, and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that of the 107 newly-listed companies by the
end of May, a large part is state-owned key ventures in the basic
industrial sector, which included Nanjing Xingang in marine
transportation, Zhenzhou Bus, Gezhouba in hydropower development,
