<HEADLINE> Vehicle Sales Drop in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 211, 680 vehicles were
sold in Thailand in the first five months this year, down 12.5
percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The slump was mainly attributed to a 20.1 percent decrease in
commercial vehicle sales and a 17.8 percent decrease in one-ton
pickup sales during the period, according to industrial sources.
</P>
<P>
However, passenger car sales saw a 6.5 increase in the five
months compared with the same period of last year.  
