<HEADLINE> Clear Water Project Unfolds in Jiangsu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Young volunteers in East China's
Jiangsu Province have recently taken part in a program to protect
local drinking water sources that have been badly polluted.
</P>
<P>
The province used to be famous for its clear rivers and
lakes. Yet, the drinking water sources have been getting
increasingly polluted due to negligence of environmental
protection during its rush for economic development.
</P>
<P>
To ease the shortage of drinking water and enhance the
awareness of environmental protection, the provincial Communist
Youth League (CYL) committee and the provincial Environment
Protection Bureau have devised a series of activities for
protecting drinking water sources.
</P>
<P>
More than one million young people added their names to a piece
of cloth bearing the characters "Creating a Green Environment for
Future Generations", as a show of support. And youngsters in
Nanjing, the capital of Jiangsu, distributed leaflets to arouse
the people's awareness of environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Lianyungang, one of the province's ports, organized students to
pick up waste from streets, rivers and harbors.
</P>
<P>
"Students have been asked not to throw things into rivers,
lakes, and reservoirs," said a head of the Jiangsu Provincial
Young Volunteers' Association. And young people are being asked to
form groups on weekends or holidays to provide information on
environmental protection in factories, enterprises and
villages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
