<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Hong Kong Opens in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition on Hong
Kong's return to China opened here today, two weeks before China
resumes the exercise of sovereignty over the region on July 1,
ending Britain's 150-year colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is composed of four parts -- Hong Kong's
history, Hong Kong people's patriotic enthusiasm, efforts made by
the Chinese government to resume the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong and Deng Xiaoping's "one country, two systems" concept.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition was co-sponsored by the Chinese Embassy in
Romania with the Romanian Foreign Ministry and Culture Ministry.
More than 400 dignitaries attended the opening ceremony, including
Chairman of the Chamber of Deputies (house of representatives) Jan
Diaconescu.
</P>
<P>
Diaconescu said Hong Kong's return to China was a major world
event and had been achieved through peaceful means, which was an
inspiration in settling international disputes.
</P>
<P>
He praised China for its patience and foresight in settling the
Hong Kong issue and termed Hong Kong's return as China's "great
political victory".
</P>
<P>
Ilie Verdet, chairman of the Romanian Socialist Labor Party,
the last foreign guest to meet the late Chinese Premier Zhou
Enlai, also delivered a speech at the ceremony. He attributed Hong
Kong's return to the increase in China's national strength.
</P>
<P>
Florea Dumitrescu, executive chairman of the Romanian-Chinese
Friendship Association, also attended the ceremony. The
Association's Secretary General Ion Dobrica told Xinhua
correspondents that Hong Kong's return had let justice prevail and
had set a good example for Macau's return and the reunification of
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
