<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic quake measuring 4.8 on
the Richter scale shook the town of Bengkulu on Indonesia's
Sumatra island Tuesday afternoon, reports reaching here today
said.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of fatalities or material damage so far.
</P>
<P>
Armin Paimin, head of the local geophysics station in
Kepahiang, said the temblor's epicenter was 33 kilometers deep
southwest in the Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
The quake, the 55th to happen in Bengkulu so far this year,
lasted 267 second.
</P>
<P>
A total of 418 quakes were monitored in the area last year.
</P>
