<HEADLINE> New Lanes to Reduce Traffic Jams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Public transportation vehicles
will have their own lanes along Chang'an Avenue in Beijing
starting from June 25, today's China Daily cited the city's
traffic authorities as saying.
</P>
<P>
Starting then, the far-right lanes for motor vehicles in both
directions from Dawang Bridge through Dongdan Crossroad and Xidan
Crossroad to Xinxing Bridge will be designed as special lanes for
public transportation between 6 am and 8 pm every day.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Beijing Municipal Public Security and Traffic
Administration said such lanes will exclusively be for buses,
trolley buses and mini-buses allowed to operate by traffic
administration departments.
</P>
<P>
All other motor vehicles are forbidden to drive or park on
these lanes, he added.
</P>
<P>
The demarcation of China's first such special lanes began on
Chang'an Aveune on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
According to bureau statistics, about 340,000 passengers use
East Chang'an Avenue and West Chang'an Avenue each day.
</P>
<P>
With the sharp rise in traffic flow in the capital city in
recent years, traffic jams have become increasingly serious and
have drawn complaints.
</P>
<P>
The municipal traffic administration has taken a series of
measures to improve Beijing's traffic situation including adopting
a policy of giving priority to public transportation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
