<HEADLINE> Central China Province Reports Record Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Hunan province, in central China,
has reported a good harvest of summer grain, and the output is
estimated to reach 860,000 tons, an all-time high.
</P>
<P>
The province has reaped 27 percent more wheat, barley, potatoes
and beans, up 27 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of rape seeds is expected to increase 15 percent to
1.09 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the acreage under grain and rape seeds was
much bigger than last year.  
</P>
