<HEADLINE> Muster Ousted in the Heineken Trophy Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSEL, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Thomas Muster of
Austria did little to boost his grasscourt confidence by wounding
up the first major upset victim Tuesday in the Heineken Trophy
tournament played in Holland.
</P>
<P>
Muster, a clay-court specialist, never found his footing on
Rosmalen's slippery grass and lost 6-4, 6-2 to 51st-ranked
Moroccan Karim Alami.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Michael Chang started slowly against 57th-ranked
Frenchman Fabrice Santoro, but came back to win 4-6, 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Among the big names hoping to sharpen their strokes for
Wimbledon which is opening next week, the Wimbledon champion and
home favourite Richard Krajicek brought about a convincing show by
ousting countryman Paul Haarhuis 7-5, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Jonas Bjoerkman of Sweden struggled into the second
round past Jan Kroslak of Slovakia, 5-7, 7-5, 6-1, but Marc Rosset
was another seeded loser. Czech Martin Damm ousted the fifth seed
from Switzerland 6-1, 7-6 (7-5).
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Richey Reneberg of the United States had to
pull out with a knee problem when he was losing 7-5, 1-0 to Czech
Daniel Vacek. 
</P>
