<HEADLINE> Russia to Set up Military Police in Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Russian defense ministry said
today that the armed forces will set up special military police to
strengthen the fight against crimes.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Kulakov, director of the military service bureau of
the Russian army's Headquarters of the General Staff, said that
the decision to set up the military police was made because of the
serious domestic crimes that are affecting the internal security
of the army, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kulakov warned that the criminal organizations are attempting
to contact servicemen so as to get weapons and ammunition from
them.
</P>
<P>
The new military police, consisting of 10,000 servicemen, will
be responsible for tracking down and arresting the servicemen who
have broken the law. 
</P>
