<HEADLINE> 450 Billion Yuan Planned For Five-Year Pollution Control in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China will use 1.2 to 1.3 percent
of its gross national product (GNP) for pollution control during
the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000), according to Xie
Zhenhua, administrator of the National Environmental Protection
Agency (NEPA).
</P>
<P>
