<HEADLINE> Southwest China Expressway Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A 138.5-km expressway in southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has become operational,
and the road links Guilin, its capital, with Liuzhou, an
industrial city in the region.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the expressway, the first in Guangxi, started
in October 1993, and it cost a total of 1.86 billion yuan, the
"China Tourism News" reports.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities say that the road is expected to promote
Guilin's tourism industry, and help with local economic expansion.
</P>
<P>
The per km cost of the expressway stands at only 13.4 million
yuan, the lowest in the country, even though it was built under
sophisticated geographical and geological conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
