<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UFO Seen in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Three policemen who were
travelling in a vehicle in the central province of La Pampa,
Argentina, said they were followed by a bright flying object that
they suspected it was an unidentified flying object (UFO).
</P>
<P>
The event occurred last Saturday but was not published by
the press until Tuesday. The policemen were identified as David
Gallego, Jose Cerna y Pilar Badal who were all travelling from
Telen to Victoria, in the province of La Pampa.
</P>
<P>
According to the policemen, they first thought that the
unidentified flying object was just the moon.
</P>
<P>
"It was an enormous semioval light, orange colored and with a
beam of light shining upwards and it followed us for 13
kilometers, said the witnesses.
</P>
<P>
The UFO emerged from inside a mountain and flew in the same
direction as the police car and then surged ahead southward to
disappear into the Caldenal mountains once again.
</P>
<P>
The police said that neither their car nor their radio
equipment experienced any mechanical failure at any time.
</P>
<P>
The sighting of UFOs is not novel in this zone, where some time
ago three hunters were followed by a flying object with powerful
light for 200 kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
