<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast in Colombia Kills Six Police Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Six police officers were killed
and nine injured in a bomb blast in the Colombian capital Tuesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred when the officers were searching the
back of a truck for suspected contraband goods just outside a
police station, said a police official.
</P>
<P>
Buildings nearby were also seriously damaged by the blast.
</P>
<P>
The official told local reporters that five died at the scene
and the sixth died at hospital.
</P>
<P>
He added that he did not believe that the explosion was an
intentional one or directed against the police, as the truck had
been towed from the main square in Bogota. 
