<HEADLINE> China's Leading TV Maker Sets Sales Promotion Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Changhong Electronics Group,
China's leading TV manufacturer in Southwest China's Sichuan
Province, has set a goal to bring in at least 18 billion yuan in
sales this year, a big jump from 12.5 billion yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Changhong, based in the city of Mianyang, has led the country
in production and sales of color TVs for eight consecutive
years. The group sold 4.8 million color TVs in 1996.The Chonghong
brand overtook Japan's Panasonic to clinch the largest
market share of 27 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The group plans to invest 2.3 billion yuan to expand its
production scale and technological improvement this year in a bid
to clinch 30 billion yuan in business turnover by 1999.
</P>
<P>
Over the next three years, the group will increase its annual
production capacity to eight million color TVs from the current
six million.
</P>
<P>
It also intends to be listed among the world's top 500
multinational firms early in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The group exports its products to more than 20 countries and
regions in Southeast Asia, Europe and Africa. Over the next three
years, it is to set up technological and trade information centers
at home to keep pace with the international development trend.
</P>
</TEXT>
