<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scenic Site to Hold International Tourist Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The '97 China Lushan International
Tourist Festival will be held from July 8 to 10, according to the
"China Tourism News".
</P>
<P>
The festival will be jointly sponsored by the provincial
government of Jiangxi, the city government of Jiujiang, and the
Administration Bureau of Mount Lushan.
</P>
<P>
Lushan is a famous mountain in Jiujiang, in east China's
Jiangxi Province. It rises abruptly on the plain, and is regarded
as a good summer resort. Due to its beauty and fine location, it
was associated with many historical events.
</P>
<P>
Jiujiang will hold a business fair at the same time. Also held
will be a Jiangxi folklore show, an exhibition of movies and TVs
related to Lushan, and calligraphical and photo exhibitions on
Jiujiang and Lushan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
