<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Cracks Down on Illegal Pyramid Selling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China has banned more than 200
enterprises from organizing multi-layer pyramid selling and
uncovered more than 500 cases of illegal pyramid schemes.
</P>
<P>
The country has promulgated the provisional regulations on the
management of pyramid selling in a bid to standardize the practice
that, if it is done well, may help save advertising and
circulation fees. But there have been many enterprises that had
attempted to take the law in their own hands and continued their
illegal practices. They included the Zhongshan Zaifa Industrial
Co., the Dongguan Xingtian Co. and the Harbin Dongfang Jewelry
World.
</P>
<P>
An official from the State Administration for Industry and
Commerce said that the enterprises took advantage of the special
practice of pyramid schemes to cheat consumers, spread
superstitious ideas and cultural trashes, infringe upon the rights
and interests of consumers and disrupt normal economic order, thus
affecting the social stability.
</P>
<P>
"This is both an economic and a political issue," said the
official.
</P>
<P>
The pyramid selling is still in the stage of experiment and the
consumers are not mature psychologically and easy to be taken in
as they are eager to get rich quickly, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said that his Administration will continue the efforts to
enforce strictly the regulations on the management of pyramid
selling and come down mercilessly on illegal schemes that are
harmful to both the economy and the society. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
