<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tauziat, Williams Advance in Eastbourne Women's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Nathalie Tauziat of France
eliminated fifth-seeded Mary Joe Fernandez 7-6 (7-5), 7-5 in the
first round of the Eastbourne women's tennis tournament on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Tauziat was much better on grass than Fernandez and she came
to the net frequently to beat Fernandez, the 1996 runner-up of
the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Tauziat will play Venus Williams in the second set. Williams
advanced after beating Chanda Rubin 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Williams took advantage of Rubin's four unforced errors in the
10th game and went on to win the set 7-6 (7-5).
</P>
<P>
Williams and Rubin exchanged breaks early in the second set.
Williams again broke Rubin in the 10th game and wrapped up the
match 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded Romanian Irina Spirlea beat Argentina's Ines
Gorrochategui 6-0, 3-6, 6-4 while eighth-seeded Brenda
Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands ousted Czech Helena Sukova
6-3, 7-6 (7-3) earlier on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
