<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Villages Ink Pumping Stations Agreement with German Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Provincial Science and
Technology Commission has signed an agreement with a German
association on helping 100 villages in the less-developed areas of
China's Zhejiang and Sichuan provinces build hydraulic ram pumping
stations that use neither fuel nor electricity before the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
According to experts, the novel piece of pumping equipment is
based on the principle that the pressure of water flowing in a
pipe will increase sharply when the flow area is suddenly
reduced. Consequently, the water rises to a higher place.
</P>
<P>
The device consumes neither fuel nor electricity, and is
suitable for mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
The Bremen Overseas Research and Development Association of
Germany began the cooperative effort with Zhejiang in 1987.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, more than 40,000 people in 60 villages of Zhejiang
and Sichuan provinces have benefited from the project.
</P>
</TEXT>
