<HEADLINE> Camenzind Wins First States of Tour of Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Oskar Camenzind of Switzerland took
the first stage of the Tour of Switzerland cycling race at
Romanshorn, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Camenzind won the first statg, a 7.2-kilometer time-trial, in a
time of 8 minutes, 57.47 seconds. Leon Van Bon of the Netherlands
finished 3 seconds behind for the second place. Roberto Petito of
Italy came home third with 5 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Tony Rominger of Switzerland was in the downpour and finished
37 seconds behind the winner.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's second stage will be a 193-km ride from Romanshorn
to Basle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
