<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentine Coach Under Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Horacio Coredero, the
Argentina-born coach of the Costa Rican national soccer team, is
under intense fire after his army suffered two losses in Copa
America which are currently being played in Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica was drubbed 5-0 by Brazil in its first cup match
last Saturday and trounced again 4-1 by Colombia on Monday, which
has effectively sent them home.
</P>
<P>
Local media was philosophic about their national boys' defeat
to World Champion Brazil and even admitted that Costa Rica was
playing out quality soccer, especially during the first hour of
the game.
</P>
<P>
But its loss to Colombia changed the tone of the
critics. "Shame" and "Pitiful" was the verdict from the national
press for the two group match humiliations.
</P>
<P>
Cordero, whose relations with the press have always been tense,
is receiving media shellings. He is being panned for employing
offside-defence tactics which is dull and lackluster and for using
players in positions to which they are not accustomed.
</P>
<P>
Yet the Argentine is fighting against all the odds by
insistting that the results do not reflect the true difference
between Costa Rican and South American soccer powerhouses.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica has only Mexico to face in their remaining group
match in Santa Cruz on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
