<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuerten Beaten in Nottingham Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- French Open champion Gustrro
Kuerton of Brazil suffered an early exit in the Nottingham men's
tennis tournament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kuerton was beaten 6-1, 7-5 by big-serving Greg Rusedski of
Britain in the pre-Wimbledon tournament.
</P>
<P>
Kuerton could not get to grips with the slippery surface and
won only three points in the first set which last for only 18
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten rallied in the second set and earned a couple of break
points. But he eventually lost the second set 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten said he had a lot to learn about playing on grass.
Kuerten is seeded 11th at Wimbledon which starts next week.
</P>
<P>
Eighth seed Todd Woodbridge of Australia was eliminated on
Tuesday as he lost to Byron Black of Zimbabwe 6-2, 2-6, 6-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
