<HEADLINE> UN GA Approves President of Ireland as Head of UNHCR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly of the
United Nations today approved the appointment of the President of
Ireland as the head of the Office of the United Nations High
Commissioner for Human Rights (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
Mary Robinson, born in 1944, will serve a four-year term of
office at the rank of Under-Secretary-General.
</P>
<P>
Mary Robinson took office in 1990. As head of state, she has
placed special emphasis on the needs of developing countries and
supported the work of international NGOs responding to
humanitarian crisis, notably in Somalia and Rwanda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
