<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Launches $500 Mln Bond Issue in Euromarket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today launched a 500 million U.S. dollar bond issue on
the Euromarket with a maturity date of June 27, 2002.
</P>
<P>
Lehman Brothers and J.P. Morgan are the joint leading managers
of a syndicate of 15 international banks for the issue, which was
priced at 101.327 percent and pays an annual coupon of 6.375
percent.
</P>
<P>
Proceeds of the issue will be incorporated into the ordinary
capital of the IDB for investments in the social and economic
development of Latin America and the Caribbean. 
</P>
</TEXT>
