<HEADLINE> European Shares End Sharply Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended sharply lower today.
</P>
<P>
Britain's benchmark FTSE-100 share index registered its biggest
one-day drop in more than two months as worries about the contents
of the UK budget preoccupied investors, dealers said. The FTSE-100
closed at 4,682.2, down 62.9 points.
</P>
<P>
German Shares ended sharply lower amid what traders said was
nervous market sentiment with no new data around to help lift
spirits on the floor of the Frankfurt bourse. The DAX-30 index
closed at 3,741.48, down 23.63 points.
</P>
<P>
In Pairs, the CAC-40 index closed at 2,762.60, down 33.27
points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
