<HEADLINE> Campaign to Downlist Minke Whale Loses Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The countries advocating for the
downlisting of the minke whale from appendix one to appendix two have
to try again in two years after losing the fight by 51 votes to 57 on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesperson for the Norway-based Friends of the Haapoon,
Lilian Selvik, said they lost the vote during the ongoing 10th
Conference of the Convention on International Trade in Endangered
Species (CITES) because the International Whaling Commission did not
understand the magnitude of the problem posed by the whale.
</P>
<P>
The minke whale is found in the northeast Atlantic and is
estimated to number over 100,000.
</P>
<P>
Fishing the whale, which is used mainly as a relish, was
banned by the International Whaling Commission in 1987. enditem

