<HEADLINE> Tanzania Urges More Investment From China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa has invited more businessmen from China to invest
in his country, to further cement the existing good co-operative
and friendly relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking with the out-going Chinese Ambassador to Tanzania,
Xie Youkun, who called on him at the State House today to bid him
farewell, President Mkapa said the friendly relationship
established by the leaders of the old generation, retired
President Mwalimu Julius Nyerere, late Chairman Mao Zedong and
Late Premier Zhuo Enlai should be nurtured and maintained by both
sides at present.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa said the frequent exchange of visits between the two
sides have made the bilateral relations more dynamic and
productive.
</P>
<P>
"Tanzania thanks Premier Li Peng's recent successful visit to
Tanzania and is ready to work side by side with China to give a new
impetus to the development of economic and trade ties between the two
nations by improving Tanzania's capabilities of attracting more
Chinese enterprises for various forms of co-operation of mutual
benefit," he told the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Mkapa asked the Chinese ambassador to
convey his best regards to Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Premier Li Peng, and expressed optimism that the friendship
between Tanzania and China will be further strengthened.
</P>
