<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
President Yasser Arafat arrived in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, today to
drum up support for the Palestinians in the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to hold talks with Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz on the negative developments of the Middle East peace
process, particularly the Jerusalem issue and the Israeli
settlement policy, Kuwait News Agency reported from Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Ambassador in Saudi Arabia Mustafa Deeb said that
the recent U.S. congress decision to recognize Jerusalem as
Israel's capital and to move the U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv to the
holy city would also be discussed by the two leaders.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries have termed the U.S. decision as a blockade to
the Middle East peace process which came to a halt in March after
Israel broke ground for a new settlement building in disputed
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Arafat would ask King Fahd to use his country's ties with the
United States to pressure Israel to honor its commitment to the
implementation of the Oslo peace agreements, Deeb said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will continue his tour to other Gulf Arab countries
after concluding his visit to Saudi Arabia Wednesday. 
</P>
