mark the yearly observance of Africa Refugee Day which falls on
June 20 opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition was jointly organized by the Organization of
African Unity (OAU), the Administration for Refugee and Returnee
Affairs of Ethiopia and the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Berhanu Kebede, a senior
official from the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry, noted that this
year's commemoration is marked in the midst of two events in
Africa: peaceful and democratic changes which enabled many
refugees to return home and conflicts that aggravated the tragic
humanitarian situation in the continent.
</P>
