<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of Works
and Urban Development Haile Asegida said today that the nation
needs close to 400,000 workers with basic construction skills for
the implementation of the development program.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the parliament, the minister said the quality
of construction works in Ethiopia has substantially deteriorated
over the past 20 years owing to the shortage of trained manpower
in basic construction skills.
</P>
