<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of Labor
and Social Affairs Hassen Abdella today stressed the need for
implementation of the national program of action for children and
women.
</P>
<P>
Opening a seminar here introducing the program which was
launched yesterday by President Negasso Gidada, the minister said
Ethiopian women experience excessive hardships as a result of
social, cultural, economic and psychological pressures which are
exacerbated by poverty and backwardness.
</P>
<P>
The minister said about 17,000 Ethiopian women of child
bearing age die every year of complications associated with
pregnancy and child birth.
</P>
<P>
Maternal malnutrition ranged from 10 to 38 percent leading
low-birth-weight of infants, he said, adding that the total
fertility rate stood at 7.7 children per woman while family
planning acceptance rate was only four percent.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the seminar, representative of the United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF) Rrn Tuluhungwa said maternal mortality,
with death from pregnancy and childbirth related causes, still
stands at an annual figure of over 700,000 and the needs of
children at risk of exploitation, abandonment and abuse are not
adequately answered and remain a major challenge, particularly in
the developing world. 
</P>
