<DOCNO> XIE19970618.0321 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Close Embassy in Brazzaville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The State Department said on
Tuesday that the United States will temporarily closing its
embassy in Brazzaville and pull out its remaining embassy staff.
</P>
<P>
"We simply can't protect them any more given the deteriorating
security situation," spokesman Nicholas Burns said at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
Burns said Washington was not severing diplomatic relations
with the Republic of Congo and was not closing the embassy
permanently. The United States decided to close its embassy in
Brazzaville because fighting between rivaling factions are still
under way and the danger for embassy personnel is increasing.
</P>
<P>
He said the 12 embassy staff will fly out on Wednesday
morning from Brazzaville airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
